Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Soak your @bamboo skewers{4} in cold water (this will prevent them from burning).

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries
(no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop two thirds of the @garlic cloves{3}(divided) (unpeeled) into a small
piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it.

Roast the garlic parcel on the baking tray with the chips until soft,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Peel and grate the remaining garlic clove (or
use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @chermoula spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if
you'd prefer things milder), lemon zest, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp}
and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs with the remaining garlic.

Add the @British beef mince{240%g}, season with pepper and mix together with your
hands.

Shape into sausage shapes, 2 per person. Flatten to make koftas and thread a
skewer through each one.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Transfer the koftas to a large baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your
oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the garlic has roasted and cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it
out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}. Mix in the @Greek style natural yoghurt{50%g}
and season with salt and pepper.

While the koftas bake, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks and add to a
medium bowl with a squeeze of lemon, the @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the dressing and a
drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with salt and pepper, then mix well.

When the fries are cooked, crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{30%g}.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the tomatoes
and toss to coat in the dressing.

Share your chermoula koftas between your plates and drizzle over the roasted
garlic yoghurt.

Serve the fries and salad alongside.

Enjoy!